## Execute commands on xscreensaver state change

```perl
               #!/usr/bin/perl

               my $blanked = 0;
               open (IN, "xscreensaver-command -watch |");
               while (<IN>) {
                   if (m/^(BLANK|LOCK)/) {
                       if (!$blanked) {
                           system "sound-off";
                           $blanked = 1;
                       }
                   } elsif (m/^UNBLANK/) {
                       system "sound-on";
                       $blanked = 0;
                   }
               }

```

